verbose_text: As shown in XREF_FIG, high K + -ACSF resulted in a slight, but not significant (P> 0.05 ANOVA), increase in annexin V staining in WT astrocytes that was prevented by exposing the cells to high K + -ACSF containing 300 muM BzATP.
